    <string name="guide_title">Setup Guide</string>
    <string name="guide_header">IOT STATION CONNECTION &amp; INSTALLATION GUIDE</string>
    <string name="guide_desc">Please follow the steps below to set up and configure your monitor station correctly.</string>
    <string name="guide_image_placeholder">Illustration Placeholder</string>
    <string name="guide_step1_title">Power up IoT device</string>
    <string name="guide_step1_desc">Plug the power cable into the IoT station, then connect to a stable power source (like a 5V adapter, mini solar station, or power bank). When the LED on the central control board starts blinking, the device is started and ready for setup.</string>
    <string name="guide_step2_title">Connect Wi-Fi for device</string>
    <string name="guide_step2_desc">Open Wi-Fi settings on your phone, find and connect to the local network emitted by the IoT station (e.g., Flood_Station_Setup). After connecting, a configuration page will automatically appear. Enter your local network SSID and password to give the station internet access.</string>
    <string name="guide_step3_title">Install device at monitoring location</string>
    <string name="guide_step3_desc">Fix the station at the monitoring area (bridge, culvert wall, or river embankment). Important: The ultrasonic sensor must point vertically down to the water. No obstacles should block the sensor\'s path. Ensure the location is within Wi-Fi range connected in Step 2.</string>
    <string name="guide_step4_title">Configure station on app</string>
    <string name="guide_step4_desc">Open the flood warning app, go to Map and select your new station. Go to Station Settings (enter admin password if required), recalibrate \"Total Height\" (actual distance from sensor to bottom) and set \"Warning\" and \"Danger\" thresholds.</string>
    <string name="guide_step5_title">Complete and Run System</string>
    <string name="guide_step5_desc">Congratulations, setup is complete! Switch to Home or Analytic screen. When you see actual water level updates and AI-predicted trend graphs, your station is officially active to protect the community.</string>
